---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
// Layout components
import Navbar from '../../components/layout/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/layout/Footer.astro';

// Home components
import Banner from '../../components/wedding-destination/Banner.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<Layout title='Destination Wedding Guide' lang={lang}>
  <Navbar lang={lang} />
  <main class='min-h-screen'>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section aria-label='Main banner'>
      <Banner lang={lang} />
    </section>

    <!-- Guide Section -->
    <section aria-label='Unique events' class='my-16 md:my-32'>
      <div
        class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between items-center flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 md:gap-12'
      >
        <div class='w-full md:w-1/2'>
          <h2 class='text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl mb-8 md:mb-12'>
            <span class='text-[#bba882] block font-extrabold'
              >The Realistic and Aesthetic Guide</span
            >
            <span class='text-[#49ac9d] text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black'
              >for a Destination Wedding with Impeccable Logistics</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class=''>
            There are weddings. And then there are <span class='text-[#49ac9d]'
              >the weddings that matter</span
            >. The ones that don't just celebrate love, but dress it up, set it,
            serve it with signature cocktails and close with a standing ovation. If you're
            going to cross borders to get married, make it worth creating something
            worthy of being remembered—and photographed—for the right reasons. These
            are not simple ideas. They are commandments for the couple who understands
            that a destination wedding is much more than choosing an exotic location
            and hoping the sunset does the work.
            <span class='text-[#49ac9d]'
              >Being in love is not enough. You also need to have taste.</span
            >
            Let's begin:
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            In a destination wedding, courtesy and logistics dance together with
            delicacy. Should guests pay for their trip? Yes, if the
            experience is worth it. The key is to <span class='text-[#49ac9d]'
              >offer clarity from the first email:
            </span> detail dates, itinerary and suggested rates from the start.
            It's not mandatory to pay for everyone, but it is your duty <span
              class='text-[#49ac9d]'
              >to facilitate everything at the level of a five-star hotel
              concierge.</span
            > Negotiate room blocks at hotels with preferential rates, propose
            closed packages and accompany each message with a promise: "Your only
            task will be to celebrate." And if you have essential guests with limited
            budgets, then: subsidize, surprise or support. Because if they're going
            to fly for you... let it be to land on something unforgettable.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class='w-full md:w-auto aspect-video'>
          <iframe
            class='w-full h-full'
            src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/izm011a5e54?si=gMpdVONt-Rz51oTW'
            title='YouTube video player'
            frameborder='0'
            allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
            referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin'
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Who Pays Section -->
    <section aria-label='Who pays what?' class='my-16 md:my-32'>
      <div
        class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between items-center flex-col md:flex-col gap-8 grid-cols-2'
      >
        <div>
          <h2
            class='text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-[#bba882] block font-extrabold text-center'
          >
            Who pays what?
          </h2>
          <h3
            class='text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-[#49ac9d] font-black text-center mt-2'
          >
            An editorial (and mathematical) rule
          </h3>
        </div>
        <p class='text-center w-full md:w-8/12 lg:w-6/12 mx-auto px-4'>
          No, you're not required to cover flights and hotel for 80 people.
          But you also can't send an invitation without clear instructions and
          expect everyone to smile from the plane. Here's a basic
          formula:
        </p>

        <div class='w-full flex justify-center px-4'>
          <div class='overflow-x-auto max-w-full'>
            <table class='border-collapse overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full md:min-w-[600px]'>
              <thead class='bg-[#49ac9d] text-third'>
                <tr>
                  <th class='px-3 md:px-6 py-3 md:py-4 text-left font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>Concept</th>
                  <th class='px-3 md:px-6 py-3 md:py-4 text-left font-extrabold text-xs md:text-base leading-tight md:leading-normal'>
                    <span class='hidden md:inline'>Estimated value per person (USD)</span>
                    <span class='md:hidden'>Value per person (USD)</span>
                  </th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class='bg-[#333638] text-third'>
                <tr class='border-b border-[#49ac9d]/20'>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 text-sm md:text-base'>Flight from Miami</td>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>$320</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class='border-b border-[#49ac9d]/20'>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 text-sm md:text-base'>Hotel 3 nights</td>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>$240</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class='border-b border-[#49ac9d]/20'>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 text-sm md:text-base'>Partial meals</td>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>$100</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 text-sm md:text-base'>Transfers & extras</td>
                  <td class='px-3 md:px-6 py-2 md:py-3 font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>$40</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
              <tfoot class='bg-[#49ac9d] text-third'>
                <tr>
                  <th class='px-3 md:px-6 py-3 md:py-4 text-left font-extrabold text-sm md:text-base'>Total per guest</th>
                  <th class='px-3 md:px-6 py-3 md:py-4 text-left font-extrabold text-lg md:text-xl'>$700 USD</th>
                </tr>
              </tfoot>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class='text-center w-full md:w-8/12 lg:w-6/12 mx-auto px-4'>
          Now multiply it by 2 if they come as a couple:<span
            class='text-[#49ac9d]'
          >
            $1,400 USD.
          </span>It's a considerable expense. That's why,<span class='text-[#49ac9d]'>
            plan as if you were a boutique hotel with a cultural agenda.
          </span>
        </p>
        <div class='w-full md:w-auto aspect-video mx-auto'>
          <iframe
            class='w-full h-full'
            src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/izm011a5e54?si=gMpdVONt-Rz51oTW'
            title='YouTube video player'
            frameborder='0'
            allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
            referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin'
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Logistics Strategies Section -->
    <section aria-label='Logistics strategies' class='my-16 md:my-32'>
      <div
        class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between items-center flex-col md:flex-col gap-8 grid-cols-2'
      >
        <div>
          <h2
            class='text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-[#bba882] block font-extrabold text-center'
          >
            Logistics strategies
          </h2>
          <h3
            class='text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-[#49ac9d] font-black text-center mt-2'
          >
            Elegant and Sensible
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div
          class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between items-center flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 grid-cols-2'
        >
          <div class='flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8'>
            <div class='w-full md:w-1/2'>
              <h4 class='text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-[#49ac9d] font-black mb-4'>
                Hotel blocks: your best card
              </h4>
              <p>
                Negotiate group rates with 2 or 3 nearby hotels (of
                different categories). Make sure to include breakfast, transfer
                to the event and late checkout. It's an elegant and practical
                gesture
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class='w-full md:w-auto aspect-video'>
              <iframe
                class='w-full h-full'
                src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/izm011a5e54?si=gMpdVONt-Rz51oTW'
                title='YouTube video player'
                frameborder='0'
                allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
                referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin'
                allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Should I Pay Section -->
    <section
      aria-label='Should I pay something to my guests?'
      class='my-16 md:my-32'
    >
      <div
        class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex flex-col md:flex-col gap-8 grid-cols-2'
      >
        <div>
          <h2 class='text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-[#bba882] block font-extrabold'>
            Should I pay something to my guests?
          </h2>
          <h3 class='text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-[#49ac9d] font-black mt-2'>
            The unwritten rule is this:
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div
          class='bg-[#333638] text-third w-full md:w-10/12 lg:w-1/2 p-5 rounded-l-lg rounded-br-lg'
        >
          <h4 class='text-[#49ac9d] font-extrabold text-lg md:text-xl'>You should cover:</h4>
          <ul class='list-disc ml-5 space-y-1'>
            <li>Welcome kit (arrival gift)</li>
            <li>Transportation to the event venue</li>
            <li>Food during the wedding (cocktail, dinner, after party)</li>
            <li>Activities if they're part of the main event</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class='flex justify-start md:justify-end'>
          <div
            class='bg-[#333638] text-third w-full md:w-10/12 lg:w-1/2 p-5 rounded-l-lg rounded-br-lg'
          >
            <h4 class='text-[#49ac9d] font-extrabold text-lg md:text-xl'>
              You can consider covering (if they're few):
            </h4>
            <ul class='list-disc ml-5 space-y-1'>
              <li>
                Partial accommodation for key guests (parents, grandparents,
                godparents)
              </li>
              <li>An extra lunch or brunch the next day</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class='bg-[#333638] text-third w-full md:w-10/12 lg:w-1/2 p-5 rounded-l-lg rounded-br-lg'
        >
          <h4 class='text-[#49ac9d] font-extrabold text-lg md:text-xl'>
            You're not obligated to cover:
          </h4>
          <ul class='list-disc ml-5 space-y-1'>
            <li>Flights</li>
            <li>Meals outside the event</li>
            <li>Personal expenses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class='flex justify-start md:justify-end'>
          <div
            class='bg-[#333638] text-third w-full md:w-10/12 lg:w-1/2 p-5 rounded-l-lg rounded-br-lg'
          >
            <h4 class='text-[#49ac9d] font-extrabold text-lg md:text-xl'>Elegant example:</h4>
            <ul class='list-disc ml-5 space-y-1'>
              <li>
                You have 50 guests. You decide to support with one hotel night for
                10 key people.
              </li>
              <li>Cost per night per double room: $80 USD.</li>
              <li>Total: 10 rooms x $80 = $800 USD</li>
              <li>A gesture worth gold... but doesn't ruin your budget.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class='w-full md:w-auto aspect-video mx-auto'>
          <iframe
            class='w-full h-full'
            src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/izm011a5e54?si=gMpdVONt-Rz51oTW'
            title='YouTube video player'
            frameborder='0'
            allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
            referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin'
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- How to Communicate Section -->
  <section
    aria-label='How to communicate without seeming rude?'
    class='my-16 md:my-32'
  >
    <div
      class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between items-center flex-col md:flex-col gap-8 grid-cols-2'
    >
      <h2
        class='text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-[#bba882] block font-extrabold text-center'
      >
        How to communicate without
        <span class='text-[#49ac9d] font-black text-center block mt-2'
          >seeming rude?</span
        >
      </h2>
      <p class='text-center w-full md:w-8/12 lg:w-6/12 mx-auto px-4'>
        Here's an example of editorially correct text for your digital Save the Date:
      </p>
      <p
        class='text-center w-full md:w-8/12 lg:w-6/12 mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-5 bg-[#333638] text-third rounded-3xl font-extrabold'
      >
        "We're thrilled to have you for an unforgettable weekend in
        the heart of Colombia's Coffee Region. We've reserved a block of rooms at
        special rates at partner hotels. A complete guide will be sent to you
        soon so you can enjoy without worries."
      </p>

      <p class='text-center w-full md:w-8/12 lg:w-6/12 mx-auto px-4'>
        Then, in the logistics guide, you can detail that travel and accommodation
        are at each attendee's expense, but that you'll have special
        activities, transportation to the event and courtesy details included.
      </p>
      <div class='w-full md:w-auto aspect-video mx-auto'>
        <iframe
          class='w-full h-full'
          src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/izm011a5e54?si=gMpdVONt-Rz51oTW'
          title='YouTube video player'
          frameborder='0'
          allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
          referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin'
          allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class='flex justify-center px-4 my-12 md:my-16'>
    <button
      class='bg-[#333638] hover:bg-[#49ac9d] text-third px-6 py-4 md:px-8 md:py-5 font-extrabold rounded-3xl text-sm md:text-base transition-colors'
      >Contact us for more advice</button
    >
  </div>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
